Qt for Python APIs expose both exclusive enumeration values and QFlags masks. JC Lib documents every advanced choice and enables multi-selection only for compatible mask-style parameters.

Examples:
- exclusive enum: `Qt.TimerType.PreciseTimer`;
- event-loop mask: `QEventLoop.ProcessEventsFlag.ExcludeUserInputEvents | QEventLoop.ProcessEventsFlag.ExcludeSocketNotifiers`;
- I/O mask: `QIODevice.OpenModeFlag.WriteOnly | QIODevice.OpenModeFlag.Text`;
- socket bind mask: `QAbstractSocket.BindFlag.ShareAddress | QAbstractSocket.BindFlag.ReuseAddressHint`.

Do not combine values when the popup remains single-selection: those entries model mutually exclusive behaviors or controlled presets.
